cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel approach for human-object interaction detection using a multi-task network and evaluations on two well-known Human-Object Interaction image datasets. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the proposed method involves machine learning techniques such as metric learning and multi-task learning. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper introduces a new approach for simultaneous interaction classification for all human-object pairs using a joint multi-task network. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the proposed method can be applied to robotics applications such as human-robot interaction detection. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not involve any cryptography or security-related topics.
